sentences: Richard Thurston (born January 6, 1973), usually referred to as "Rich Thurston" is an American musician, songwriter, recording engineer and mixed martial artist.
Thurston began training as a mixed martial artist in 2003.
During his inaugural amateur fight on November 5, 2004, he dislocated his elbow while against opponent Joshua Blanchard.
In November 2006, Thurston became a professional fighter.
Blood Has Been Shed - bass (1999–2000), guitar (2000)
Blood Has Been Shed - bass (1999–2000), guitar (2000)
Walls of Jericho - touring rhythm guitar (2003)
Deep Breath - vocals, guitar, bass, drums (2020–present)
He has also lived in and performed with bands from Virginia, Connecticut, Massachusetts, California, Michigan and Ohio, the latter of which has been his home since the late 1990s.
He has also been straight-edge and vegan since the early 1990s, participating in several bands that vocalized those beliefs and ethics.
